{{Infobox monarch | name =23rd Ruler | title =Ajaw of [[Tikal]] | image = | image_size = | caption = | reign =c.635 | coronation = | full name = | predecessor =[[Animal Skull]] | successor =[[24th Ruler]] | spouse = | issue = | royal house = | father = | mother = | birth_date = | birth_place = | death_date = | death_place = | date of burial = | place of burial = | religion =[[Maya religion]] |}} '''23rd Ruler''' was an ''[[ajaw]]'' of the [[Maya civilization|Maya]] city of [[Tikal]]. He ruled c.635. Information about this ''ajaw'' and his successor [[24th Ruler]] are next to nothing. K'inich Muwaan Jol II is the best candidate to be 23rd or 24th Ruler because he could be a father of 25th ''ajaw'' [[Nuun Ujol Chaak]].<ref>Martin & Grube 2008, p.42.</ref>
