{{Infobox Politician | name = Henry Ryan Haney | image = HenryRyanHaney23.jpg | imagesize = 180px | office1 = [[Member of Provincial Parliament (Ontario)|Ontario MPP]] | term_start1 = 1872 | term_end1 = 1878 | predecessor1 = [[Lachlin McCallum]] | successor1 = [[Richard Harcourt]] | constituency1 = [[Monck (provincial electoral district)|Monck]] | party = [[Ontario Liberal Party|Liberal]] | birth_date = 1835 | birth_place = [[Pelham, Ontario]], Canada | death_date = {{death date and age|1878|11|17|1835}} | death_place = Pelham, Ontario, Canada | occupation = Physician | relations = | spouse = | children = }} '''Henry Ryan Haney''' (1835 &ndash; November 17, 1878) was an [[Ontario]] physician and political figure. He represented [[Monck (provincial electoral district)|Monck]] in the [[Legislative Assembly of Ontario]] as a [[Ontario Liberal Party|Liberal]] member from 1872 to 1878.
He served as [[coroner]] for [[Welland County, Ontario|Welland]]. He was first elected to the provincial legislature in an 1872 by-election after the sitting member, [[Lachlin McCallum]], resigned when it became illegal for members to sit in both the [[House of Commons of Canada]] and the Ontario legislature. Haney was reelected in 1875 but unseated on appeal; he was elected in the by-election that followed and represented Monck until his death in 1878.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://familysearch.org/pal:/MM9.1.1/JDVN-LJN |title=Henry Haney |publisher=Family Search.org}}</ref>
